                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240916-157-off855 t18240916-157-crimeloc860"></join>, with Mr. Gross's <rs id="t18240916-157-viclabel861" type="occupation">little daughter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240916-157-victim1361 t18240916-157-viclabel861"></join>, Amelia - that shop is near my master's - Wilmore was with me. I saw the prisoner<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182409160064"></xptr>come and take the beads from the baby's neck; he did not undo the snap, but broke the ribbon. He gave them to another man, who was two or three yards from him, and said,</p>
               <p>"Here Sam!" they then walked away together; I went across, and took hold of him, and said he had the beads; he said he had not; I said he had given them to the other man - he said he would go back to him and see. I would not let him go, or he would have run away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-157-person1364">
                  SUSANNAH 
                  WILMORE
               <interp inst="t18240916-157-person1364" type="surname" value="WILMORE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-157-person1364" type="given" value="SUSANNAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-157-person1364" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am twelve years old. I was with Underwood, near Mr. Isaacson's shop. I took the prisoner's hand off the child's neck - he had the heads in his hand. I saw him give them to the other man, who ran away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-157-person1365">
                  JOHN 
                  ISAACSON
               <interp inst="t18240916-157-person1365" type="surname" value="ISAACSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-157-person1365" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-157-person1365" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Staffordshire dealer. On the evening of the 6th of September these two girls came to my shop, with a child in their arms - they had not left the shop more than a minute before I heard a screaming. I came out, and saw they had got hold of the prisoner's coat, and said he had taken off the child's beads, and gave them to a man who ran away.</p>
